OBJECTIVE: Specific survival estimates are needed for the increasing number of 
colorectal cancer (CRC) survivors. The aim of this population-based study was to 
determine conditional loss in expectation of life (LEL) due to CRC.
STUDY DESIGN AND SETTING: All surgically treated patients with CRC registered in 
the Netherlands Cancer Registry with stage I-III between 1990-2016, were 
included (N = 203,216). Estimates of conditional LEL were predicted using 
